#| msgid ""
#| "The Earth is round, and it is always half-illuminated by the Sun. "
#| "However, because the Earth is spinning, the half that is illuminated is "
#| "always changing. We experience this as the passing of days wherever we "
#| "are on the Earth's surface. At any given instant, there are places on the "
#| "Earth passing from the dark half into the illuminated half (which is seen "
#| "as <emphasis>dawn</emphasis> on the surface). At the same instant, on the "
#| "opposite side of the Earth, points are passing from the illuminated half "
#| "into darkness (which is seen as <emphasis>dusk</emphasis> at those "
#| "locations). So, at any given time, different places on Earth are "
#| "experiencing different parts of the day. Thus, Solar time is defined "
#| "locally, so that the clock time at any location describes the part of the "
